41
00:05:27,490 --> 00:05:30,220
SPEAKER_12: Master Fugui is going home. You take him.

112
00:11:24,509 --> 00:11:26,370
SPEAKER_12: Don't worry about her.

113
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:35,580
SPEAKER_12: Get out of my sight!

124
00:13:45,279 --> 00:13:48,149
SPEAKER_12: It's all in order, I'll be going.

125
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:54,379
SPEAKER_12: Master Fugui, don't think badly of me...

126
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:56,950
SPEAKER_12: for leaving you homeless.

127
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,590
SPEAKER_12: But I sure like that mansion of yours.

131
00:14:10,409 --> 00:14:12,710
SPEAKER_12: Master Fugui, I'm sorry...

132
00:14:12,779 --> 00:14:15,769
SPEAKER_12: but you've nothing left.
What would you wager?

133
00:14:16,110 --> 00:14:18,809
SPEAKER_12: If you're unhappy, talk to Mr. Xie.

135
00:14:21,789 --> 00:14:23,950
SPEAKER_12: What are you doing?

136
00:14:24,019 --> 00:14:26,110
SPEAKER_12: It's not over yet!

145
00:15:00,620 --> 00:15:03,120
SPEAKER_12: Not that we'd accept it as ante.

174
00:18:11,650 --> 00:18:13,450
SPEAKER_12: Both sides must sign.

183
00:19:32,059 --> 00:19:36,660
SPEAKER_12: It's valuable. Don't scratch it. Take it slowly.

184
00:19:36,730 --> 00:19:39,789
SPEAKER_12: Careful, slowly. Don't move too fast!

185
00:19:39,869 --> 00:19:41,930
SPEAKER_12: Don't break anything!

186
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:49,500
SPEAKER_12: Your mother's not well.
Go now, for her sake.

228
00:24:09,470 --> 00:24:11,769
SPEAKER_12: This old home of yours is great.

229
00:24:12,180 --> 00:24:14,369
SPEAKER_12: Warm in winter, cool in summer.

231
00:24:19,420 --> 00:24:22,009
SPEAKER_12: I've given up the puppet troupe.

232
00:24:22,119 --> 00:24:23,519
SPEAKER_12: Have a seat.

233
00:24:25,619 --> 00:24:28,990
SPEAKER_12: I don't gamble anymore.
Don't want to end up like you.

242
00:25:10,829 --> 00:25:13,930
SPEAKER_12: I never had to beg
when I ran the puppet troupe.

243
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,190
SPEAKER_12: Earn your money yourself.

244
00:25:17,539 --> 00:25:19,529
SPEAKER_12: Put together a troupe.

275
00:31:12,500 --> 00:31:14,619
SPEAKER_12: Get it out of my sight then.

285
00:32:26,140 --> 00:32:28,759
SPEAKER_12: Way to go, Chunsheng!

286
00:32:28,839 --> 00:32:30,170
SPEAKER_12: Take this.

287
00:32:36,279 --> 00:32:39,299
SPEAKER_12: - Where'd you get them?
- Off the corpses.

292
00:32:58,029 --> 00:32:59,359
SPEAKER_12: It really is booze!

332
00:37:10,219 --> 00:37:13,780
SPEAKER_12: - On one of the wounded.
- It's a killing field.

485
00:56:50,159 --> 00:56:51,530
SPEAKER_12: Enough?

486
00:56:51,699 --> 00:56:54,690
SPEAKER_12: Still not enough? Okay, I'll fill it right up.

511
00:59:02,460 --> 00:59:04,690
SPEAKER_12: Apologize. Say you were wrong.

512
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:07,489
SPEAKER_12: Now!

513
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:11,530
SPEAKER_12: I'm talking to you.

514
00:59:13,239 --> 00:59:14,969
SPEAKER_12: - Are you going?
- No.

515
00:59:15,239 --> 00:59:17,269
SPEAKER_12: - Are you going or not?
- No!

516
00:59:17,750 --> 00:59:20,039
SPEAKER_12: - I'm telling you to go!
- No!

737
01:24:25,050 --> 01:24:27,350
SPEAKER_12: You can't keep them. Burn them!

830
01:32:10,619 --> 01:32:12,920
SPEAKER_12: You've gone to so much trouble.

953
01:44:15,539 --> 01:44:16,640
SPEAKER_12: Who?

954
01:44:16,710 --> 01:44:18,039
SPEAKER_12: Chunsheng.

955
01:44:23,149 --> 01:44:24,779
SPEAKER_12: What do you want?

956
01:44:26,949 --> 01:44:28,850
SPEAKER_12: Come out for a second.

1193
02:02:12,520 --> 02:02:14,880
SPEAKER_12: But he was okay after the water.

